-- Japanese Bought Net 920 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   T h e r e s a   B a r r a c l o u g h
-- 2012-01-18T23:52:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-18/japanese-bought-net-920-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended Jan. 13 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 920 billion yen ($12.0 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 33.6 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 8 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 878.3 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 192.3 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 139.8 billion yen in stocks, and bought 11.2 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 343.2
billion yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Theresa Barraclough in Tokyo at   tbarraclough@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  